    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="43" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <head>No. 43.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Guzman</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the Republic of Nicaragua</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 10,
                            1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Pursuant to the conversation I had with your
                        excellency on the 7th instant, I have sent to the President of Nicaragua a
                        cable gram in which I state that the Government of the United States would
                        be <pb facs="0091" n="84" xml:id="pg_84"/> pleased to see that the-utmost
                        harmony may prevail between Nicaragua and the canal company, and that it
                        would be much gratified if all proceedings against the said company were
                        revoked.</p>
                <p>I reiterate, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. Guzman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
